When the httpclient uploads a file, the Content Disposition will have duplicate filename names, causing the file upload to fail and the server to return a 403 error.
When uploading files, if using:
content.Add(streamContent, "file", Path.GetFileName(filePath));
Adding files and generating Content Disposition will result in duplicate filename:
Content-Disposition: form-data: name "file": filename "2025-03-18 172728.png
filename* utf-8%222025-03-18 172728.png%22
And it can be avoided through the following methods:
byteContent.Headers.ContentDisposition = new ContentDispositionHeaderValue("form-data")
{
Name = "file",
FileName = Path.GetFileName(filePath)
};
This should be a bug in httpclient
